extracted_text:
In the Central Business Zone, every building hereafter erected or structurally
altered to exceed 50 feet in height shall, above said height, be set back from the front lot line on the ratio of one
foot for each two feet rise above said 50 feet in height.
llm_outputs.rationale: This section explicitly states the height limit for buildings in the Central Business Zone. While it does not provide an absolute maximum height, it specifies that buildings over 50 feet must have setbacks proportional to their additional height.
llm_outputs.answer: 50 ft with additional setbacks required for taller buildings
